other Bank\">Open a New Account at another Bank<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/easy-steps-to-changing-banks\/#close-your-old-account-to-change-banks\" title=\"Close Your Old Account to Change Banks\">Close Your Old Account to Change Banks<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/easy-steps-to-changing-banks\/#consider-mobile-and-online-banking\" title=\"Consider Mobile and Online Banking\">Consider Mobile and Online Banking<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/easy-steps-to-changing-banks\/#find-enticing-offers-to-open-a-new-account-when-switching-banks\" title=\"Find Enticing Offers to Open a New Account When Switching Banks\">Find Enticing Offers to Open a New Account When Switching Banks<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"are-there-legitimate-reasons-to-change-my-bank-to-another-one\"><\/span>Are There Legitimate Reasons to Change My Bank to another One?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Maybe you think that you deserve better customer service or more access to innovative technological banking tools. It could be that you\u2019re tired of high transaction fees and want to be given more <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-multiple-payment-gateways-help-merchants-sell\/#:~:text=Anyone%20looking%20to%20expand%20their%20business%20to%20a%20global%20scale%20should%20consider%20whether%20their%20current%20payment%20provider%20can%20handle%20such%20a%20shift\">options on financial products<\/a>. Your old bank may be outside the region you now preside in, and you yearn for branches and cash point machines in your location.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some folks get married and want to combine accounts in another bank. Changing banks is within your consumer rights, and there\u2019s no law against it as long as it\u2019s your personal finances. If you\u2019re not happy with how a bank\u2019s managing your money or their digital payments, it\u2019s better to find another service provider. Your new banking institution may even be offering rewards for switching, including cash or retail vouchers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you\u2019ve been with your old bank for some time, it\u2019s best to shop around and see what\u2019s new in the retail banking sector. You\u2019ll consider your needs while finding incentives to make the switch, such as interest perks, cash backs, or reward deals.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When changing banks, you\u2019ll see how different providers measure up to the obligations or expectations of your financial service during your account search. You\u2019ll ask to review their overdraft and interest rates, standout features of their accounts, and credit eligibility criteria.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"how-do-you-change-banks-quickly-and-painlessly\"><\/span>How Do You Change Banks Quickly and Painlessly?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Moving your money and other financial obligations is no mean task. You\u2019ll have little peace of mind until you know that you won\u2019t miss direct debits, and cheques won\u2019t bounce. Will other platforms where your current account is linked, like PayPal, become affected and will card payments be on time?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you break down this process, handling switching financial providers in manageable parts, changing banks is doable. As long as you don\u2019t let uncertainty stop you, it\u2019s easy to make a quick and painless switch to an institution that meets your needs. It doesn\u2019t make sense to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/advisor\/banking\/how-to-switch-banks-a-step-by-step-guide\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">continue in unrewarded loyalty<\/a> while you\u2019re missing out on lower interest rates or fewer transaction fees.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Initially, you\u2019ll make a list of all the automatic digital payments, subscriptions, and recurring debits you\u2019ve set up in your present account. That eliminates the chance of bills, cards, or other digital payments getting mixed up during the switch. If you\u2019re using a fintech or Neo Bank, you can print out all your digital transactions for the month or quarter.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To initiate a process of changing banks, that\u2019s quick and painless switch<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"choose-a-new-bank-for-switching-accounts-to\"><\/span>Choose a New Bank for Switching Accounts To<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Selecting a new financial provider is the most significant of the steps towards changing banks. A lousy fit could mean that you have to start the process all over again. You have multiple reasons for leaving your current bank, considered as qualities to check against with a new institution. The top priorities to pay attention to include;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Account opening and balance requirements<\/li><li>Transactional fees<\/li><li>Ease and convenience of online banking<\/li><li>Interest rate variables on your account balance<\/li><li>Branch locations<\/li><li>Cash vending machine fees and locations<\/li><li>Customer service<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Other factors you\u2019ll look at in a new bank include how they ensure your money and their performance track record. Make use of the many available switch kits online that help to match the best institution to your lifestyle and income levels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/changing-banks-open-account.jpg\" alt=\"changing banks and opening accounts\" class=\"wp-image-769\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/changing-banks-open-account.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/changing-banks-open-account-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/changing-banks-open-account-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"open-a-new-account-at-another-bank\"><\/span>Open a New Account at another Bank<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The sooner you open a new account in your preferred bank, the smoother and painless your switch. Opening an account takes less than 10 minutes, especially if you\u2019re doing it online. You\u2019ll fill out a form with your name, address, employment details, and contact information. Some banks require photo identification, and your driving license or passport will suffice.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You\u2019ll also make an initial deposit in your new account before you\u2019re issued new information and a debit or credit card. Instead of withdrawing all your funds from the old bank, leave in at least a month\u2019s bills worth of cash. That covers any <a href=\"https:\/\/lifehacker.com\/how-to-painlessly-switch-banks-1537247659\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">automatic payment processors<\/a> you may have missed to avoid lateness penalties.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, your new bank should follow up with the former institution for a statement of transactions for the last six to 13 months. That may include subscriptions or recurring fees for cloud software, streaming, rideshare, or public transport. It\u2019ll also make switches for direct credits like salary, share dividends, and welfare or pension payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your new bank will request the account and routing numbers from the institutions you\u2019re currently with for online account opening. That\u2019s used to verify deposit information from linked accounts before transferring funds. You can use this electronic link for transferring money and savings from your old banking institution.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"close-your-old-account-to-change-banks\"><\/span>Close Your Old Account to Change Banks<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you are satisfied that all transactions have transferred to your new account, you can proceed to close the old one at your former bank. As the final step in your switch, closing accounts can be done online or in-person over the phone. Some banks charge fees for this, especially if you\u2019ve closed it within a specific time frame of its opening.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can zero out any remaining balances by obtaining cash or a cashier\u2019s cheque. Your old bank might also be willing to transfer electronically to your new account. When you receive the final statement, read it carefully to ensure no deposits need transfer or other lingering payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ask for written verification from your old bank that your account is closed. That comes in handy if they allow a debit transaction, which triggers non-payment fees. Other times, zombie accounts reappear, especially in online banking, and it makes sense to sign in regularly to check that it stays closed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"consider-mobile-and-online-banking\"><\/span>Consider Mobile and Online Banking<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that your new account is set up, can you access it online or through mobile banking? That\u2019s typically your only option if you\u2019re new institution is an online-only fintech or a Neo Bank with dynamic portals.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your bank will assist with opening your profiles for online and mobile banking. You\u2019ll need to enrol or register into these portals before you can use your PIN, username, or password to log in and verify. That verification often involves <a href=\"https:\/\/www.csmonitor.com\/Business\/Saving-Money\/2017\/0207\/Why-you-might-want-to-switch-your-bank\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">two-factor authentication<\/a> using text or email. Downloading your new bank\u2019s mobile application guarantees a seamless account management experience.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"find-enticing-offers-to-open-a-new-account-when-switching-banks\"><\/span>Find Enticing Offers to Open a New Account When Switching Banks<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The bank switching guarantee ensures that your new account is up and running within seven business days. That means all your digital payments and direct debits are transferred and new cheque books or cards issued.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your new bank account is ideally from a top high street provider with various financial products as well as a high branch and cash point prevalence. You can find current basic accounts with no-frills for customers with poor credit who want stricter money management. Others come with benefits like higher-than-average savings interest or low borrowing rates for authorised overdrafts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Banks now offer in-account packages like breakdown cover, travel insurance, or exclusive discounts. Instead of buying all these products separately, it works out cheaper as part of a money-saving incentive.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>You don\u2019t need to be concerned about paperwork when changing banks, as financial providers have an agreement to make the process quick and painless.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":768,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[16,14,23],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/751"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/w